Refactor station processing logic and improve recipe handling
Replaced server-side processing timers with station attributes for better synchronization with clients. Enhanced ingredient validation for stations, refined recipe progression, and adjusted client-server state updates for responsiveness.

Refactor particle system management and improve recipe handling
Simplified particle system handling by removing pooling logic and using disposable systems. Enhanced recipe processing with detailed steps and improved UI displays in the order component for multi-stage recipes. Streamlined interaction methods and fixed naming inconsistencies (e.g., `isResult` to `isFinal`).

Refactor ingredient handling and enhance particle effects.
Refactored logic for ingredient pickup/drop with enhanced validation. Introduced craft complete effect system and improved oven particle effects for a richer visual experience. Fixed inconsistencies in particle cleanup and ingredient positioning.

Add confetti effect to GameEndScreen
Integrate the `react-confetti` library to enhance the GameEndScreen with celebratory confetti animation. Updated `package.json` and `bun.lock` files to include the new dependency. Adjusted layout styling to ensure confetti correctly overlays the screen.

Enhance interaction lifecycle and game flow handling
Added isActive state to InteractableObject for better interaction lifecycle management. Fixed issues with audio disposal, improved game cleanup logic, and correctly handled game over rendering state. Adjusted GameRoom logic to drop plates properly upon order completion.

div.div: While the demons were rising, mankind was about to become extinct. Six temples rose, and protected the last of mankind. A young boy joins the temple as a knight to save his mother. During his journey of wonders and mischief in the world of temples and demons, will he be able to ascend to become the strongest knight and inherit the throne?

A new adaption of the manga of the same name by Togashi Yoshihiro. A Hunter is one who travels the world doing all sorts of dangerous tasks. From capturing criminals to searching deep within uncharted lands for any lost treasures. Gon is a young boy whose father disappeared long ago, being a Hunter. He believes if he could also follow his father's path, he could one day reunite with him. After becoming 12, Gon leaves his home and takes on the task of entering the Hunter exam, notorious for its low success rate and high probability of death to become an official Hunter. He befriends the revenge-driven Kurapika, the doctor-to-be Leorio and the rebellious ex-assassin Killua in the exam, with their friendship prevailing throughout the many trials and threats they come upon taking on the dangerous career of a Hunter.

Back then, Dok-Ja had no idea. He had no idea his favorite web novel 'Three Ways to Survive the Apocalypse' was going to come to life, and that he would become the only person to know how the world was going to end. He also had no idea he would end up becoming the protagonist of this novel-turned-reality. Now, Dok-Ja will go on a journey to change the course of the story and save humankind once and for all.
(Source: WEBTOONS, edited)

One big fat lie and a few twisted truths.
Even in his past life, Cid's dream wasn't to become a protagonist or a final boss. He'd rather lie low as a minor character until it's prime time to reveal he's a mastermind...or at least, do the next best thing-pretend to be one! And now that he's been reborn into another world, he's ready to set the perfect conditions to live out his dreams to the fullest. Armed with his overactive imagination, Cid jokingly recruits members to his organization and makes up a whole backstory about an evil cult that they need to take down. Well, as luck would have it, these imaginary adversaries turn out to be the real deal-and everyone knows the truth but him!
(Source: Yen Press)
